# Git

Every commit in this repository must follow the rules below. If another guide (including tools that default to an all-lowercase subject) disagrees with them, **this file takes precedence**.

- Shape: Conventional Commits — `<type>[optional scope]: <Description>`.
- Subject line: after the colon, capitalize the first word of the description. Write it as a short sentence, not a forced-lowercase keyword list.
- Examples:
  - Good: `docs(specs): Add canonical status metadata`, `feat(kernel): Introduce session event envelope`
  - Avoid: `docs(specs): add canonical status metadata`
